            >, such as hyperactivity, and some dyes have even been flagged as
            possible carcinogens. The FDA has begun phasing out certain dyes,
            including <i>Citrus Red No. 2</i> and <i>Orange B</i>, while states
            like West Virginia and Texas are passing their own bans or labeling
            requirements.
